<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamabad Radio Reports 18 Killed in Kashmir Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamabad Radio Reports 18 Killed in Kashmir Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0605061394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0605061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In occupied Kashmir, clashes between the freedom 
fighters and Indian troops continue in various parts of the 
valley in which 18 more people have been killed. The clashes 
occurred in Pulwama, Punch, Baramula, (Dandarbal), Srinagar, and 
Ghazipura- Hindwara. A total strike was observed in Pulwama and 
adjoining rural areas as a protest against the killing of five 
people by Indian troops in (Guddu) village. The people in 
Nagabal also observed a strike against Indian atrocities. 
Meanwhile, Jammu and Kashmir Trade Union Front has called a 
strike on 7 and 9 May as a protest against the violation of 
human rights by the occupation forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

