<H3> <TI>   President Husayn Dismisses Intelligence Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Husayn Dismisses Intelligence Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505222794 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 2100 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505222794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait Radio Kuwait </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraqi opposition sources in Salah al-Din in northern 
Iraq have said that the head of the ruling regime in Baghdad has 
dismissed Sabir 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Duri, the director of his 
intelligence services, after the exposure of the culprits in the 
assassination of the Iraqi dissident Shaykh Talib Suhayl 
al-Tamimi in Beirut, and the involvement of the Iraqi regime's 
intelligence services in the killing of German journalist Lissy 
Schmidt in northern Iraq early last month. 

</TEXT>

