<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPK, PUK Agree To Joint Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPK, PUK Agree To Joint Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0505182494 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1530 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505182494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The two political bureaus [not further identified] 
today held a joint meeting at Salah-al-Din resort under the 
supervision of brother Mas'ud Barzani [leader of the Democratic 
Party of Kurdistan--DPK]. The following points were approved 
during the meeting: 
  1. To form a joint committee between the Patriotic Union of 
Kurdistan [PUK] and the DPK in al-Sulaymaniyah, Karkuk, and 
Qal'at Dizah, and Raniyah to end fighting and its effects there. 
  2. To send a joint committee with similar form and 
authority to Dahuk, Zakho, al-'Amadiyah, 'Aqrah, and all parts 
of (Shahbinan) to carry out the duties mentioned in the first 
paragraph. 
  3. To exchange all detainees. 
  4. Both sides should return each others offices. 
  5. To return each other's properties, machines, and 
equipment as soon as possible and without delay. 
  6. To account for troop concentration and prevent the 
mobilization of any new troops against each other. 
  7. To remove all manifestations of fighting through the 
media. Both sides are responsible for disseminating information 
in a fraternal, peaceful, and harmonious spirit. 
  8. To leave no room for any statements or words without 
approval from central authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

