<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   PUK Forces Capture Several Towns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PUK Forces Capture Several Towns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505180894 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After recent clashes between the Kurdistan 
Democratic Party [KDP] of Iraq and the Patriotic Union of 
Kurdistan [PUK], which resulted in many casualties among the 
forces of the two sides and the innocent people of the region, 
and despite the agreements between the officials of the two 
mentioned parties to refrain from attacking each other's 
offices, today the PUK forces, led by Jalal Talebani, captured 
the towns of Shaqlawah, (Panjbeyn), and Chamchamal. 
  On the other hand, many Barezani tribesmen, affiliated to 
the 
KDP, led by Mas'ud Barezani -- under the name of Barezan Corps 
-- cleared the town of Salah ad Din from the PUK and captured 
the PUK television station that covered the area. 

</TEXT>

