<F P=103> JN0505193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1145 today, President Hafiz al-Asad received 
Lebanese President Ilyas al-Hirawi, Chamber of Deputies Speaker 
Nabih Birri, Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, and Foreign 
Minister Faris Buwayz. 
  Attending the meeting were Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim 
Khaddam, People's Assembly Speaker 'Abd-al-Qadir Qaddurah, Prime 
Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi, and Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar'. 
  The talks dealt with a host of issues and regional and Arab 
developments, particularly the peace process, developments in 
its tracks, and current contacts in this regard. 
  The Lebanese officials were briefed on the contents of the 
talks U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher held in 
Damascus, and on the Syrian position which adheres to a just and 
comprehensive peace in all tracks. 
  The two sides stressed the importance of coordination and 
cooperation among the Arab parties to the peace process, and of 
their adherence to the objective set for this process. 
  The talks also dealt with issues of interest to both Syria 
and Lebanon. 
  A working lunch was also held. 
  Lebanese President Ilyas al-Hirawi returned to Beirut today. 
Also returning with him were Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih 
Birri, Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, and Foreign Minister 
Faris Buwayz. 

