<H3> <TI>   Meets With King </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With King </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0505173594 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn received Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat and the delegation accompanying him at 
the Royal Hashemite Court today. His Highness Crown Prince 
Hasan attended the meeting. 
  At the outset of the meeting, President 'Arafat extended, in 
his own name and on behalf of the Palestinian leadership, 
condolences to His Majesty King Husayn and the esteemed 
Hashemite family on the death of Queen Mother Zayn al-Sharaf. 
  President 'Arafat also briefed his majesty on the latest 
developments in the negotiations between the Palestinian and 
Israeli sides, and what has been reached in the Cairo agreement. 
He expressed the Palestinian leadership's appreciation for 
Jordan's role, particularly His Majesty King Husayn's efforts, 
in supporting and backing the Palestinian people. 
  His Majesty King Husayn reiterated Jordan's firm support for 
the Palestinian rights and the PLO in its capacity as the sole 
legitimate representative of the Palestinian people. He also 
stressed Jordan's concern about supporting the kinsfolk in the 
occupied territories, and about alleviating their suffering. 
  Attending the meeting for Jordan were Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali, the prime minister, al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, chief 
of the Royal Hashemite Court, Marwan al-Qasim, political adviser 
to his majesty the king, and Talal al-Hasan, minister of state 
for foreign affairs. On the Palestinian side were Yasir 
'Abd-Rabbuh, Yasir 'Amr, Salim al-Za'nun, father Iliya Khuri, 
and the Palestinian ambassador in Amman. 

</TEXT>

