<H4>    Kakizawa Tours Jericho </H4>

<F P=102> OW0505233994 Tokyo KYODO in English 2305 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0505233994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, May 5 KYODO -- Japanese Foreign Minister 
Koji Kakizawa toured the West Bank town of Jericho on Thursday 
[5 May], a day after he attended the signing ceremony in Cairo 
of a historic agreement on limited Palestinian self-rule for 
Gaza and Jericho. 
  He visited a local hospital in Jericho to which Japan has 
offered to supply medical equipment. Kakizawa visited Jericho 
before arriving in Amman, where he paid a courtesy call on King 
Husayn and conferred with other Jordanian leaders. 
  Kakizawa is visiting Jordan during a tour of the Middle East 
which has already taken him to Egypt and Israel. 

</TEXT>

