<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beilin on Christopher's Mediation, Accord With PLO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beilin on Christopher's Mediation, Accord With PLO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505171594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 5 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin says American 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher will return to the region 
in the middle of the month, because he is convinced peace can be 
achieved between Israel and Syria. Beilin told reporters in Tel 
Aviv that Christopher received a detailed Israeli proposal 
representing official thinking on the nature of the settlement. 
He had received the Syrian reply, which was very different from 
Israel's proposal, but was sufficiently detailed to envisage a 
common denominator between the two sides, he said. Beilin also 
said there was no serious prospect of development between Israel 
and Syria without American intervention. 
  Referring to the agreement with the PLO, Beilin stressed 
'Arafat's biggest test would be the manner of the entry of the 
Palestinian police and 'Arafat's ability to stand up to the 
opposition against him. Israel would not agree to any PLO 
agreement with Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] enabling 
Hamas to operate outside the autonomy, because it would be a 
violation of the agreement. 

</TEXT>

