<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Sources' in Washington on Christopher's Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Sources' in Washington on Christopher's Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605054494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 6 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0605054494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sources in Washington believe that U.S. Secretary 
of State Christopher's willingness to mediate between Israel and 
Syria practically ends the previous modus operandi for 
negotiations in Washington between December 1991 and the Hebron 
massacre [in February 1994]. 
  An Israeli source in Washington has said that, in the peace 
package offered to Syria, Israel did not promise a full 
withdrawal, nor did it offer a withdrawal from Majdal Shams 
first. The terms the Syrians used in their reaction to the 
Israeli proposal contained more concrete terms than in the past 
regarding the definition of peace and normalization. The 
Syrians have gone from using general terms such as 
demilitarization to using numbers, according to the source. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

