<H3> <TI>   IDF To Pursue `Ordinary' Operations in Territories </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF To Pursue `Ordinary' Operations in Territories </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605113994 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 6 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> TA0605113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by David Regev] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Great concern over the PLO 
request to delay the transfer of powers was voiced yesterday by 
members of the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] top echelons. 
Lieutenant General Ehud Baraq, the chief of staff, has recently 
stated in a cabinet meeting that a delay in the IDF withdrawal 
from the Strip is liable to provoke radical elements, who 
realize they have nothing to lose, to carry out terrorist 
attacks against IDF targets. A senior officer said yesterday: 
"On the one hand, we must start cooperating with the 
Palestinian police, and on the other, to pursue antiterror 
activities." 
  The chief of staff and the Central Command commander have 
instructed IDF commanders to pursue their ordinary operational 
activities. And indeed, a long series of operational activities 
was carried out during the past week, including the capture of 
Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and Islamic Jihad fugitives, 
searches of Palestinian homes, patrols, and ambushes. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

