<H3> <TI>   Incidents in Hebron, Jericho Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Incidents in Hebron, Jericho Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605043394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 6 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0605043394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two Molotov cocktails were thrown last night at a 
bus close to the village of Biddiya on the Trans-Samaria 
highway. No one was hurt and there was no damage. South of 
Hebron, another firebomb was tossed at a bus. Again, no one was 
hurt. 
  A Qol Yisra'el reporter says throughout the day there were 
disturbances in the Hebron, Jericho, and Tulkarm areas. 
Soldiers used tear gas and rubber bullets to disperse stone 
throwers. 
  The center of Hebron was open yesterday to commerce and 
trade. 

