<H3> <TI>   GCC, EU Foreign Ministers To Meet in Riyadh 8 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GCC, EU Foreign Ministers To Meet in Riyadh 8 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605110494 Kuwait Radio Kuwait in Arabic 1000 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0605110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait Radio Kuwait </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The foreign ministers of the Gulf Cooperation 
Council [GCC] and their counterparts in the European Union will 
arrive in Riyadh tomorrow to take part in their fifth joint 
meeting due to start on Sunday [8 May]. The GCC foreign 
ministers are expected to hold a [separate] meeting after their 
arrival to discuss items on the agenda of the [8 May] meeting. 
  GCC foreign ministry undersecretaries had met early last 
week 
to examine the draft joint statement which will be issued at the 
end of the one-day meeting. Diplomatic sources have reported 
that the statement is expected to include several topics 
relating to energy, the environment and the developmnent of 
economic relations between the two communities, in addition to 
other issues of mutual interest, foremost the security situation 
in the Gulf region in the light of the Iraqi regime's refusal to 
abide by the resolutions of international legitimacy. The peace 
process in the Middle East and the situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegivina will also be mentioned in the joint statement. 

</TEXT>

