<H3> <TI>   Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Defense Ministry Appeals for Unity </H4>

<F P=102> EA0505200094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2045 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0505200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A responsible source at the Defense Ministry has 
stated the following: In continuation of the scenario prepared 
by the gang of al-Ahmar, whose bloody appetite was stimulated 
after the aggression against the 3d Armored Brigade in 'Imran, 
this bloody gang of al-Ahmar, which thirsts for blood and 
devastation, at 8:15 tonight began to attack the Martyr Ba 
Suhayb Brigade Camp in Dhamar town. This daring brigade, in 
these decisive historic moments, is waging a fierce war against 
the enemies of the homeland and is confronting with bravery, 
death, and defiance the mercenaries of the adventurist gang of 
al-Ahmar. [passage omitted] 
  While the Defense Ministry deals with this crime, it assures 
the masses of our Yemeni people that it will remain loyal to the 
pledge by individuals of our armed forces to protect our people 
and their national and democratic options. In these historic 
moments, it calls on all the honorable sons of our people, the 
heroes of their Armed Forces and the generous forces to stand 
united to confront this imminent danger to the homeland and its 
unity, and inflict defeat on the bloody gang of al-Ahmar. Our 
people are lying in wait for them. 

</TEXT>

