<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Former Officials Urge `Prudent Intervention' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505162094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1510 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 May (MENA) -- A number of former Yemeni 
ministers and officials have called on President Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak to exert more efforts to save the Yemeni people of the 
current infighting. 
  Addressing their plea also to the leaders of Syria, Saudi 
Arabia, Jordan, Oman, and the United Arab Emirates, as well as 
the Arab League secretary general, the former officials said 
that the strife in Yemen is a result of misjudgment, 
miscalculation, and ill-advised policies. 
  'Abdallah al-Asnaj, former Yemeni foreign minister; Qasim 
Bin- 'Ali al-Wazir, former member of the Advisory Council; Major 
General 'Abdallah Juzaylan, former deputy prime minister; a 
former finance minister; a former agriculture minister; and a 
member of the Ta'izz Popular Congress, all of whom are currently 
in Cairo, signed the plea. 
  The Yemeni officials pointed out that Yemen is sinking in a 
bloodbath and that prudent intervention is needed to contain the 
crisis. 

</TEXT>

