<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting Continues; Airport Bombed; Calls for Peace Made </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    YSP Suspends House of Deputies Membership </H4>

<F P=102> EA0505200694 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0505200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The parliamentary bloc of the Yemeni Socialist Party 
[YSP] issued a statement in which it expressed its regret and 
resentment over the statement issued today by the House of 
Representatives which represented the secessionist congress and 
al-Islah blocs, and has no connection with the Constitution. 
The statement said that the House of Representatives is to be 
used to justify the war declared by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, the 
motives of which hide the secessionist lenience [as heard] of 
the forces which rejected the convention document and the 
national dialogue, and instead declared the war by attacking a 
number of brigades in the northern governorates. 
  The statement said that the declaration of the war by 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and his military dynasty, supported by the House 
of Representatives, is a disaster to our people. The statement 
declared the boycott of the meeting of the House of 
Representatives and suspended the membership until it rectifies 
its stand. 

</TEXT>

