<H4>    Fighting `Still Raging' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505173594 London MBC Television in Arabic 1702 GMT 5 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505173594 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone report by MBC correspondent Tawfiq Jazulit in </F>
Sanaa--live or recorded] 
  [Text] Political and military sources have reported to us 
that the fighting has extended to the areas of Ta'izz, Abyan, 
al-Bayda', and Aden. Also, warplanes belonging to the Yemeni 
Socialist Party carried out air strikes against Sanaa, Ta'izz, 
and al-Hudaydah, as well as the airports and vital targets in 
the three towns. 
  Fighting is still raging. Various types of air force and 
ground weapons are being used by the two sides. Meanwhile, calm 
returned to Dhamar after the surrender of the Basahib camp and 
the joining of its troops to the northern forces. 
  Seven military brigades belonging to the north are now 
advancing toward Aden to tighten their control on it. The MBC 
team is at this very moment in the Sanaa television building and 
southern warplanes are flying over to attack the building. 
Antiaircraft fire is intercepting the raiding planes. 

</TEXT>

