<H4>    Parliament Decides To Dismiss al-Bid, Others </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505194094 Paris AFP in English 1935 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, May 5 (AFP) -- The Yemeni parliament decided 
to dismiss Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid and other southern 
leaders, blaming them for the outbreak of civil war on Thursday 
[5 May], the official news agency SABA said. 
  The parliament, meeting in Sanaa in the absence of southern 
deputies, ruled that "any action or decision taken by 'Ali Salim 
al- Bid or his supporters is from now on considered illegal and 
not binding." 

</TEXT>

