<H4>    Defense Minister Dismissed, To Stand Trial </H4>

<F P=102> JN0505204094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Presidential Council Decision No. 8", issued by the </F>
Presidential Office in Sanaa 5 May] 
  [Text] The Presidential Council today made the following 
decision: 
  Presidential Council Decision No. 8 of 1994 regarding the 
dismissal of Brigadier General Defense Minister Haytham Qasim 
Tahir from his post and turning him over for questioning on the 
charge of committing a number of [word indistinct]. 
  The chairman of the Presidential Council, after referring to 
the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen, and seeing that Brig. 
Gen. Haytham Qasim Tahir committed war crimes associated with 
his position, and with reference to the public interest, [word 
indistinct] the Presidential Council decided: 
  Article 1. Defense Minister Haytham Qasim Tahir shall be 
dismissed from his post, questioned, and put on trial in 
accordance with Article 111 of the Republic of Yemen's 
Constitution for the crimes he committed while carrying out his 
duties. 
  Article 2. This decision takes effect on the date of its 
release and publication in the official gazette. 
  Released at the Presidential office in Sanaa on 25 Dhil 
Qi'dah, 1414 Hejira, corresponding to 5 May, 1994. 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of the Presidential Council 

</TEXT>

