<H4>    Al-Bid's `Special Guards,' Others Join Northern Army </H4>

<F P=102> JN0605124694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0605124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source has issued a statement in which it 
said a number of unionist officers and soldiers in units under 
the command of the rebel secessionist elements in the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] are continuing to join the ranks of the 
army of unity and constitutional legitimacy. Yesterday, all the 
personnel of the 1st Artillery Brigade in the Yarim region and 
the Khurafi camp that includes the personnel of the special 
guards of al-Bid and the personnel of the military police 
battalion joined their brothers in the units of the Armed 
Forces, which are protecting unity and democracy, after they 
discovered the hellish plan of the secessionist clique that 
wants to disrupt the homeland. 
  The military source pointed out in its statement that our 
Air 
Force defenses confronted all the treacherous, hostile air raids 
on the capital, Sanaa, and the cities of Ta'izz, al-Hudaydah, 
and Ma'rib--raids that targeted vital and strategic 
installations in these cities in order to terrorize peaceful 
citizens. 
  The source also clarified that Colonel Jawad Muthanna, 
commander of the Ba Suhayb Brigade, and the brigade's staff were 
arrested yesterday after they sparked sedition in the city of 
Sanaa. 

</TEXT>

