<H3> <TI>   League Chief Calls For End to Fighting in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Chief Calls For End to Fighting in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0605053794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1942 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0605053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 May (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has issued an urgent appeal to the 
brothers in Yemen, calling on them to refrain from fighting, 
exercise self-restraint, and close their ranks. Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid warned the Yemenis that partition and civil war 
would only bring ruin and hardship. 
  The secretary general said that Arab countries and the 
league's General Secretariat are following the escalation of the 
situation in Yemen with concern and that they hope to see it end 
soon. 
  Yesterday Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid telephoned President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and offered to send a high-level delegation to 
Yemen to help contain the crisis. However, the delegation could 
not travel to Yemen because of the shelling of Sanaa Airport. 
  Today Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid received a telephone call from 
Yemeni 
Prime Minister Dr. Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas. The secretary 
general urged al-'Attas to seek an end to the fighting to 
preserve the safety, security, and stability of brotherly Yemen. 

</TEXT>

