<H3> <TI>   Arab Liberation Front Condemns Self-Rule Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Liberation Front Condemns Self-Rule Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0505121994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0505121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Central Committee of the Arab Liberation Front 
[ALF] has condemned the signing of the Gaza-Jericho agreement 
between the PLO and the Zionist entity. 
  A spokesman for the ALF Central Committee has stated that 
the 
ALF condemns this agreement, announces that it rejects it, and 
that it will not comply with all that results from it. This is 
because this agreement is the result of successive concessions 
that began at Madrid and continued until the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement was reached. 
  The statement [as heard] said: We are confident that such 
agreements cannot cancel our historic right to our entire 
homeland or prevent our people from continuing their struggle as 
part of a comprehensive Arab confrontation that will undoubtedly 
come under the banner of the immortal Mother of Battles led by 
the nation's knight and hero and the Arab mujahid leader, Saddam 
Husayn. 

</TEXT>

