<H3> <TI>   PLO To Withdraw Fatah Members, Weapons From Lebanon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO To Withdraw Fatah Members, Weapons From Lebanon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505140494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1338 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0505140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, 5 May (MENA)--The PLO will be taking steps 
to withdraw its weapons and armed men from Lebanon and to 
eliminate all evidence of its military and semi-military 
presence on Lebanese territories. 
  Palestinian sources have said that the PLO will withdraw 
between 200 and 500 Fatah members in the first stage along with 
weapons and military equipment. 
  The sources added that they expect the Lebanese army to 
deploy in the areas where the Palestinian camps are situated 
with the aim of strengthening the state's authority over all the 
areas in Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

