<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes Israeli-PLO Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Welcomes Israeli-PLO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505190394 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Algeria expresses satisfaction at the 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement that was signed in Cairo yesterday 
on the implementation of Palestinian self-rule in the occupied 
territories. 
  A Foreign Affairs Ministry spokesman considers this 
agreement 
to be important and a new qualitative phase on the road to a 
just and comprehensive settlement of the Middle East issue, 
which takes into account the legitimate rights of the 
Palestinian people and their sovereignty, and their right to 
establish an independent state with Jerusalem as its capital. 
  The Foreign Affairs Ministry spokesman adds that Algeria, 
which renews its complete solidarity with Syria, Jordan and 
Lebanon, is of the view that the peace process in the region 
necessarily requires the unconditional Israeli withdrawal from 
all occupied Arab territories. 

