<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the escalation of clashes between brothers 
in the Republic of Yemen, His Excellency President Zine El 
Abidine Ben Ali today telephoned his brother president, Liamine 
Zeroual, the head of state of the Algerian Republic and chairman 
of the Presidential Council of the the Arab Maghreb Union. His 
excellency the president suggested that the Union would 
undertake urgent efforts and make representation to the Yemeni 
leaders in an effort to achieve conciliation between them, and 
to spare the blood of the fraternal Yemeni people and safeguard 
the unity and safety of their territory. 
  His excellency the president also entrusted the foreign 
minister to consult with his Algerian counterpart and to contact 
the Arab League secretary general in order to discuss the means 
of a common action, to make efforts to restore harmony and 
understanding between the Yemeni leaders, and to save Yemen from 
the dangerous complications now threatening its unity and 
security. 

