<F P=104>  Tunis Tunis-7 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by Foreign Ministry; date not given]- </F>
  [Text] Following the signing of the agreement on self-rule 
between the Palestinians and the Israelis, the Foreign Ministry 
has issued the following statement: 
  Tunisia has noted with satisfaction today's signing between 
the PLO chairman and the Israeli prime minister on the agreement 
to implement the Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and Jericho, 
which should initiate the implementation of the Declaration of 
Principles signed in Washington on 13 September 1993, bolster 
the peace process in the Middle East, and which is an important 
step toward a just and comprehensive solution in order to 
guarantee the legitimate rights of the struggling fraternal 
Palestinian people and its right to lead a dignified life in a 
sovereign state. 
  Tunisia, which has always been tireless in maintaining and 
consolidating the independence of the Palestinian 
decision-makers, supporting the Palestinian people's just cause, 
and following up the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations, is hoping 
that the new agreement will give fresh momentum to continue the 
peace process at all costs in order to bring about the total 
Israeli withdrawal from all occupied Arab territories and peace 
in the region in accordance with the UN resolution and 
international legality. 

</TEXT>

