<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-088 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Islamic Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   ICO Secretary General Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ICO Secretary General Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505012694 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 2130 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0505012694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamic Conference Organization [ICO] Secretary 
General Dr. Hamid al-Ghabid expressed his deep satisfaction and 
welcoming of the signing in Cairo of the agreement between the 
PLO and Israel on the implementation of the agreement on 
transitional self-rule in the Gaza Strip and Jericho. 
  In a statement today, he said that this agreement was an 
important turning point in the history of the Palestinian people 
and a decisive step in the course of its just struggle, during 
which immense sacrifices were made toward the achievement of its 
legitimate rights including the right to return, the right to 
self determination, and the setting up of its independent 
Palestinian state on its national territory with Jerusalem as 
its capital. 
  The secretary general welcomed the courageous and wise steps 
taken by the PLO under the leadership of His Excellency 
President Yasir 'Arafat in defense of the proud Palestinian 
people's rights and interests during this stage of hard talks. 
  Dr. Hamid al-Ghabid stressed the Muslim nation's fundamental 
and constant support of the Palestinian people in its fight to 
regain its basic national rights. 
  He called on the international community to provide all 
forms 
of support to the Palestinian people during this historic period 
of constructing and developing its vital utilities and 
infrastructure and its national social and economic institutions 
as the fundamental pillars for its national authority on its 
land, thus bolstering security and stability in the region. 
  The ICO secretary general praised the efforts made by all 
parties to the peace process that contributed toward achieving 
this agreement, particularly the efforts made by Egyptian 
President Husni Mubarak in this regard as well as the peace 
process cosponsors, the United States and Russia. He called on 
them to continue their efforts in order to achieve tangible 
progress on all other Syrian, Jordanian, and Lebanese peace 
tracks in a way that will guarantee a full Israeli withdrawal 
from all occupied Arab territories and the establishment of a 
comprehensive and just peace in the Middle East on the basis of 
international legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-58733 </DOCNO>
