<H3> <TI>   Musa Comments on Plans To Stop Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Comments on Plans To Stop Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0605102894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0945 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0605102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 May (MENA)-- Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
announced that Egypt will submit a number of proposals to the 
emergency meeting of the Arab League ministerial council to be 
held on Saturday [7 May]. They will include the possibility of 
the League's intervention to end the fighting and monitor the 
situation in Yemen. 
  In statements today, Musa said Egypt is contemplating 
submitting a proposal to send Arab troops to Yemen upon the 
League's decision, and after obtaining Yemen's approval. 
  Musa said he has contacted the foreign ministers of Saudi 
Arabia, the Sultanate of Oman, and the United Arab Emirates on 
developments in Yemen and the ministerial council meeting. 
After contacting President Mubarak and a number of Arab 
leaders, Musa urged Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid to call an emergency meeting. 

</TEXT>

