<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Refugees Talks To Start Next Month </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Refugees Talks To Start Next Month </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505143594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 5 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The talks regarding the return of the Arabs who 
became refugees in 1967 will start in approximately one month. 
The number of these refugees is estimated by Israel to be about 
200,000. The talks will be held in the framework of the joint 
Israel-Palestinian-Egypt-Jordan committee, as stipulated by the 
Declaration of Principles. 
  The talks regarding the clauses which were not finalized 
before the signing of the agreement with the PLO will resume in 
Cairo within one week. The negotiations regarding Palestinian 
early empowerment will also start within one week. 

</TEXT>

