<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Official: Arms Control Talks `Successful' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Official: Arms Control Talks `Successful' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505162294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 5 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The document of principles of the multilateral arms 
control committee will be discussed in a working meeting of the 
committee members in a special session in Vienna. This has been 
decided at the conclusion of this round of talks, held in Qatar. 
Qol Yisra'el correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that another 
working team of the multilateral committee will convene in 
France in the near future to discuss other issues which have not 
been finalized. 
  David 'Ivri, director general of the Defense Ministry, 
described the Qatar meeting as successful. He noted that among 
other things, it was decided to hold a naval search and rescue 
maneuver. David 'Ivri noted that the Saudis and several other 
parties tried to delay the rate of progress, because they 
believe the talks are proceeding too fast. 

</TEXT>

