<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saudi Arabia Refuses To Host Multilateral Committees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saudi Arabia Refuses To Host Multilateral Committees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0605112894 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 6 May 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0605112894 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Sulayman Nimr report: "Saudi Arabia Refuses To Host </F>
Multilateral Negotiations Committees"] 
  [Excerpts] Doha -- The meeting of the Arms Limitation and 
Regional Security Committee arising from the multilateral 
negotiations concluded in Doha yesterday. [passage omitted] 
  Prince Turki Bin-Muhammad Bin-Sa'ud, head of the Saudi 
delegation, has told AL-HAYAH that Saudi Arabia refuses to host 
any meeting of the committees arising from the multilateral 
negotiations or to attend any of their meetings in Israel. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

