<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Head: Yemen Situation `Extremely Grave' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Head: Yemen Situation `Extremely Grave' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0605205694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2049 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0605205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 May (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid described the current situation in 
Yemen as "extremely grave." 
  In a statement to be published tomorrow, Saturday, by 
AL-WAFD, the mouthpiece of the opposition Wafd Party, Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid said every effort is being exerted to stop the 
fighting. He said the Egyptian initiative to resolve the Yemeni 
crisis aims to reach a solution, noting that this depends on 
acceptance by the Yemeni parties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

