<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's al-Dali Welcomes Arab League Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's al-Dali Welcomes Arab League Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705104794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1010 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0705104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 May (MENA)-- Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today received Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz 
al-Dali, member of the Political Bureau of the Yemen Socialist 
Party [YSP] and personal envoy of Yemeni Vice President [title 
as received] 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  Following the meeting, al-Dali stated that the urgent 
meeting 
of the Arab League Council is a positive step toward solving the 
Yemeni crisis. He said he hopes the meeting will stop the 
bloody war between northern and southern Yemeni troops in good 
time. 
  He added that the YSP supports any step the brothers at the 
Arab League take and the Egyptian initiative on Yemen. 
  Al-Dali said the current infighting in Yemen is not a 
domestic but rather a pan-Arab affair, adding that the YSP will 
demand Arab assistance if the Yemeni parties fail to stop the 
fighting. 
  Touching on the Egyptian proposal to send Arab peace-keeping 
forces to Yemen, al-Dali remarked that the YSP will welcome this 
if it becomes necessary, even if Yemeni leaders refuse to stop 
fighting. 
  He appealed to all Yemeni leaders and brothers in Egypt and 
other Arab states to take action to end the ongoing fighting in 
Yemen. 

</TEXT>

