<F P=103> LD0605214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh Saudi Arabian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Details on the situation in 
the occupied Gaza Strip and Jericho and the reactions to the 
agreement on implementing Palestinian self-rule are in the 
following report from our correspondent in the occupied 
Palestinian territories: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] [Passage omitted] On the 
reasons 
behind the Palestinian request to delay assuming authority from 
the Israeli side, I met Dr. Samir 'Abdullah, member of the 
negotiating team, whose name appeared on the list of the 
upcoming national authority. He said: 
  [Begin recording] ['Abdullah] It is obvious that there is a 
weakness in the Palestinian preparedness. Preparations for this 
day were not made in a correct manner, and this has led to the 
delay. 
  [Correspondent] This request for the delay was the subject 
of 
criticism by the Israelis and probably by some international 
sides. This is attributed to the inability of the Palestinians 
to assume the responsibilities for which they have been calling 
for a long time. 
  ['Abdullah] In my view, the criticism is clear. There is 
bitter criticism in the Palestinian camp. The Palestinian camp 
and people were waiting for the moment of withdrawal of the 
Israelis from the occupied territories, but it seems that the 
leadership in Tunis has not prepared itself properly for this 
moment, though it was expected that the Palestinians would 
assume authority quickly. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

