<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Denies National Authority Membership Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th Denies National Authority Membership Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805104894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 0930 GMT 8 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, head of the Palestinian 
negotiating team, has denied reports that he apologized to PLO 
Chairman Yasir 'Arafat for not wanting to join the new 
Palestinian national authority which will run the self-rule in 
Gaza and Jericho. 
  In an interview with our correspondent Sa'id Mu'addi, Sha'th 
said he was not nominated to join this authority in the first 
place and that news agency reports on this issue were only 
rumors. He noted that no appointments have been announced yet. 

