<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-089 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th on Police Arrivals, Appointment `Rumors' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th on Police Arrivals, Appointment `Rumors' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805112794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 0945 GMT 8 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview With Dr. Nabil Sha'th, head of the </F>
Palestinian negotiating team to the Cairo talks, in Tunis, by 
Sa'id Mu'addi in the studio; date not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, reports say you 
apologized to Yasir 'Arafat regarding your appointment in the 
Palestinian national authority. How true are these reports? 
  [Sha'th] I was not nominated for this authority and I have 
not apologized. I do not know the source of these two reports. 
Thus far, no appointments have been announced and no one has 
been asked to do anything. I have not apologized to anyone for 
anything. These are only rumors. 
  [Mu'addi] The PLO leadership is discussing the formation of 
the Palestinian National Authority. How far have these 
discussions gone? 
  [Sha'th] I believe that in the next few days, maybe in the 
next three days, these names will be announced and given to the 
Israeli Government. 
  [Mu'addi] Let us move to the Israeli-Palestinian agreement 
signed last week in Cairo. What are the future steps, 
particularly regarding the deployment of Palestinian police 
force in Gaza and Jericho? 
  [Sha'th] These forces are now massing in Rafah, on the 
Egyptian side of the border, and in Jordan, to prepare to cross 
into Gaza and Jericho. Naturally, there is some delay resulting 
from the civil war in Yemen and the fact that planes cannot fly 
in Libyan airspace. Our troops in Yemen will have to move by 
land to Saudi Arabia first, and our troops in Libya will have to 
move by land from Libya to Rafah. This will naturally cause 
some delay. But, troops are now in Rafah waiting for permission 
to cross. Troops are also in Amman preparing to move to the 
Jordan Valley and cross the Allenby Bridge. I think that in the 
next week or 10 days, these troops will enter to form the bulk 
of the Palestinian police force. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil, regarding the talks on refugees, this 
issue has drawn some reaction in Israel. What did the Oslo 
Agreement stipulate in this regard? 
  [Sha'th] The Oslo Agreement is very clear. However, there 
are some people on the Israeli right who do not wish to read, or 
if they do read, do not wish to understand the agreement. The 
agreement says the four-sided committee--comprising Jordan, 
Egypt, Israel, and the Palestinian authority--will discuss the 
return of refugees who left after 1967 from only two aspects: 
Establishing the measures for their return and the measures to 
protect security and public order. There are no restrictions on 
the numbers or the principle of the return of these individuals. 
The issue concerns only measures. 
  [Mu'addi] When will the proceedings of the four-sided 
committee start? 
  [Sha'th] The decision was made in the letters exchanged 
between Chairman 'Arafat and Prime Minister Rabin that Israel 
and the PLO should invite Jordan and Egypt to the first meeting 
within a month after signing the agreement. That will be before 
4 June. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, thank you. 
  [Sha'th] Thank you. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-58793 </DOCNO>
