<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister's Office Denies Missile Test Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister's Office Denies Missile Test Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805104694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Prime Minister's Office [PMO] has refuted report 
appearing in a section of the press that 13th test of 
surface-to-surface missile Prithvi, scheduled for the weekend, 
has been called off following instructions from PMO. An official 
spokesman said in New Delhi today that there is no question of 
stopping the missile program and no such instructions were 
given. He said the report as well as the inference is 
absolutely false. 

</TEXT>

