<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabbani Forces Said To Capture Baghlan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabbani Forces Said To Capture Baghlan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805163994 Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1600 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0805163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1600 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The city of Baghlan, north of Kabul, was captured by 
forces of Borhanoddin Rabbani. According to a report by the 
Central News Unit, fierce fighting continues in Baghlan province 
between forces loyal to the president and the joint forces of 
General Dostam and Afghan Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar. 
  Sources opposed to the government, while confirming that 
intense battles are continuing in the Baghlan province, blame 
the government forces for starting the fighting. 
  Another report indicates that fighting is intense in the 
vicinity of the town of Pol-e-Khomri in Baghlan province, and 
forces loyal to the president are trying to capture this town. 

</TEXT>

