<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet, Knesset To Consider PLO Agreement 11 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet, Knesset To Consider PLO Agreement 11 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0805155194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 8 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0805155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet has authorized an additional 4,000 
Palestinians from the territories to work inside Israel in 
tourism, industry, and agriculture. The cabinet ministers were 
told that the right-wing Knesset members [MK's] would be 
evacuated from the ancient synagogue in Jericho. 
  Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin noted that a precedent for such 
action had already been set. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that the 
cabinet will convene on Wednesday [11 May] to ratify the 
agreement with the PLO. The agreement will also be brought 
before the Knesset for approval. 
  The cabinet also discussed the decision to promote Efi Fein 
to the rank of brigadier general after Minister Yosi Sarid 
raised the matter. 

</TEXT>

