<H3> <TI>   International Observer Force Arrives in Hebron </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International Observer Force Arrives in Hebron </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0805103994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 8 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0805103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The international force of observers is beginning 
its duties in Hebron today. The 160-strong force, including 
support staff and experts, comes from Norway, Denmark, and Italy 
and was agreed on by Israel and the PLO following the Hebron 
massacre in February. Mark Weiss reports from Hebron: 
  [Begin Weiss recording] I am speaking from the Hebron 
Municipality building. The international observer force has 
arrived in the town and has just been welcomed by Mayor 
al-Natshah at the Municipality building. He expressed [word 
indistinct] that the people will feel safer because of the 
arrival of the temporary international presence. He expects all 
the population to cooperate despite reports of threats from 
Islamic fundamentalists. The mayor told me that tomorrow a 
meeting will be held between the international observers and the 
Islamic fundamentalists in the town. The mayor said he believed 
their arrival will reduce the level of violence in the city. 
The observers arrived in a fleet of white Fiat Uno cars flying 
a white flag. They are all dressed in smart white uniforms. 
For most of them it is the first time they have arrived in the 
town and they are actually due to begin their work tomorrow. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

