<H4>    Presidential Palace Said in Flames </H4>

<F P=102> NC0605142794 Paris AFP in English 1418 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0605142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, May 6 (AFP) -- Southern warplanes fired 
missiles at the presidential palace in the Yemeni capital Sanaa 
on Friday [6 May], officials said here. 
  The attack left the palace in flames, said the officials 
from 
the Yemeni Socialist Party of deposed vice-president 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid. 
  His forces have been battling the northern army of President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. 

</TEXT>

