<H3> <TI>   Southern Forces Attack Targets in Sanaa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Southern Forces Attack Targets in Sanaa </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sanaa Denies Palace Attacked </H4>

<F P=102> NC0605182694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1813 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0605182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 6 May (MENA)--A responsible Yemeni source 
this evening denied reports that the Presidential Palace in 
Sanaa came under air strikes from the South Yemeni Air Force. 
  In a statement to SABA'', the northern source said that the 
forces in the south fired five long-range Scud missiles at 
Sanaa, noting that two of the missiles fell in mountainous 
areas, one fell near the airport in Sanaa, and two missiles 
failed to explode. 
  The source affirmed that the missiles caused no material or 
human losses. 

</TEXT>

