BFN 

  [Text] Dubai, United Arab Emirates, May 8 (AFP) -- Troops 
loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih on Sunday captured the 
south's main military airport, 50 kilometres from the port city 
of Aden, Western diplomatic sources said. 
  The sources in the region said Al-'Anad was the only 
military 
airport around the southern stronghold of Aden, although the 
south has a second base in the Hadhramaut, 700 kilometres (420 
miles) to the east. 
  The northern forces have the port city trapped in a "pincer 
movement," one diplomat said. 

</TEXT>

