<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 7 May (WAKH) -- The southern leadership in 
Aden has asked the United Nations to intervene to stop the 
fighting in Yemen. 
  Radio Aden reported this evening that Prime Minister Haydar 
Abu-Bakr al-'Attas last night telephoned UN Secretary General 
Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali and informed him of the bloody incidents 
in Yemen. The radio said Dr. Butrus-Ghali stressed UN keenness 
to help Yemen to stop the fighting and overcome the crisis. 
  The radio pointed out that al-'Attas asked Yemen's permanent 
UN representative to hold consultations with the president and 
members of the Security Council to coordinate international 
efforts to support the efforts of the Arab League to end the war 
in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

