<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dubai, United Arab Emirates, May 6 (AFP)--The 
southern Yemen Socialist Party (YSP) called for a ceasefire on 
Friday to halt its two-day-old civil war against the northern 
forces of President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Aden Radio said. 
  The radio, monitored by Gulf news agencies, said the YSP 
based in the southern port city of Aden "accepts a ceasefire in 
response to calls from Arab and foreign countries." 
  "This favourable response is dictated by the interests of 
the 
Yemeni people, whose lives, belongings, unity, armed forces and 
economic installations must be preserved," the radio said, 
quoting a YSP statement. 

