94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0605211594 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa has rejected the dispatch of Arab forces to 
stop the war in Yemen, saying that what is happening in Yemen is 
a domestic affair and could be decided internally, according to 
sources of the General People's Congress, which is led by 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. 
  Salih dismissed the Yemeni oil minister and the Aden 
governor, both of whom belong to the Yemeni Socialist Party led 
by 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  Our correspondent Tawfiq Jazulit reported a short time ago 
that south Yemeni fighter planes staged several raids tonight on 
Sanaa. Six Scud missiles fell on the city during the day while 2 
northern planes raided Aden. The northerners have announced 
that they are preparing to launch an attack on Aden on several 
fronts. 

</TEXT>

