<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Urges Support for Accord Document, Democracy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Urges Support for Accord Document, Democracy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0705163494 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0705163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, the deputy chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] Central Committee, has confirmed that the 
Yemeni people will successfully pass through this test of unity 
and democracy, just as they did the test of the September and 
October revolutions. 
  He explained during a news conference that the Yemeni people 
are strong because of the cause they support, and that no matter 
how much the secessionist al-Ahmar gang tries to fabricate 
issues, militarize the crisis, and derail the homeland, the 
political forces and national consensus will remain on the 
correct path which we all chose on 20 February. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid said: Man is Yemen's foundation. 
Hence, our strength lies with men and with those causes which 
men support. Random missile and cannon fire do not amount to 
any kind of strength, and they will not prevent the masses from 
raising their heads proudly and refusing to yield to the wishes 
and sicknesses of domineering gangs. We are stronger, our 
people are stronger -- we shall not abandon the march on the 
path that we chose -- the path of unity and democracy, the path 
of stability. 
  The brother deputy chairman of the Presidential Council and 
secretary general of the YSP pointed out in the course of his 
speech that the party had sacrificed much on behalf of the 
people. It had confronted the evil gangs so that they would not 
plunge the country into conflict. He pointed out that these 
concessions to the evil gangs have now been exhausted, and that 
the YSP stands united with the people. He confirmed that the 
situation is getting better. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid pondered what might be happening 
in 
Sanaa and many other areas, pointing out that the northern gangs 
have cut off communications both inside and outside the country 
so that people cannot communicate. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid stated that our legitimacy is 
derived from the people, and that the legitimacy of the media, 
which is being imposed on the people, is transient. He said 
that this legitimacy will only last for a couple of days, and he 
doubted the ability of some people to impose it for thirty days. 
  He emphasized the importance of cohesion to the internal 
front and to the nationalist forces, and stressed commitment to 
the processes of unity, democracy, multipartyism, and 
nondiscrimination between the citizens, wherever they live in 
any governorate. Whoever supports the pledge and accord 
document, national cohesion, and peaceful, democratic struggle, 
is with us in any governorate. The deputy chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the YSP explained 
that instructions have been given for opening a camp in Lahj 
Governorate for whoever wants to join the ranks of unity and 
democracy. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid denied reports being disseminated 
by the hostile media on the strike against the Dhamar 
electricity station. He pointed out that the Republican Guard 
in Dhamar carried out this act. He emphasized that the forces 
of unity and democracy did not and will not hit any vital 
targets, since these belong to the people. But the forces of 
unity and democracy will search for the gang and its palaces, 
hideouts, and nests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

