<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Orders General Mobilization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Orders General Mobilization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0705202994 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1800 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0705202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Haytham Qasim Tahir has issued a 
ministerial order calling for the general mobilization of human 
and material reserves in all governorates. The first article of 
the order provides for the declaration of a general mobilization 
of human and material reserves in all governorates. The third 
article of the order (?commits) the general administration to 
mobilize its reserves and branches in the governorates to 
implement the mobilization tasks for which they are responsible, 
and to organize callups and scrutinize specializations in 
accordance with unit needs for human and material resources with 
effect from 6 May. 
  The sixth article of this order stipulates that all military 
personnel must proceed to their military units within a period 
of 24 hours. The seventh article of the order commits the 
general administration to mobilize its reserves, and through its 
branches in the governorates to coordinate with large 
organizations, the public sector, and government organizations 
to ensure the execution of the tasks stipulated in this order. 
  The eighth article of the order stipulates that the order 
will become operative with effect from its date of issuance, and 
that it shall be published in the official gazette. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

