<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Says Al-Bid Told Jordan's Husayn 'Ready for Dialogue' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Says Al-Bid Told Jordan's Husayn 'Ready for Dialogue' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0905102694 Amman JORDAN TIMES in English 9 May 94, p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0905102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman JORDAN TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yemeni Vice-President 'Ali Salim al-Bid on Sunday 
contacted His Majesty King Husayn saying he was ready for a 
political dialogue with President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Aden 
Radio said in a report monitored by the British Broadcasting 
Corporation. There was no Jordanian confirmation of the report. 
  King Husayn brought President Salih and Vice-President 
al-Bid, as well as other Yemeni political leaders together in 
Amman in February to sign a reconciliation and reform agreement. 
However, the accord was not implemented and the king said last 
month that Jordan was leaving a joint military commission 
entrusted with separating the northern and southern army units. 

</TEXT>

