<DATE1>  8 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Warns Against Price Increases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Warns Against Price Increases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805044294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0335 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Supply and Trade warns all wholesale 
and retail dealers in the Republic of Yemen about the need to 
comply fully with the prices for all commodities that prevailed 
before the emergency was declared in the country. Anyone 
breaching this warning will be find, have his trade registration 
confiscated, and his shop closed. He will also be subject to 
direct imprisonment. 
  The ministry will launch a supply monitoring campaign to 
control commodity prices. A team from the Ministry of Supply 
and Trade, the Interior Ministry, and the capital's municipality 
will take part in the campaign. The ministry's Aden branch and 
the supply offices in the republic's governorates should also 
form committees from the offices, the ministry's monitors, and 
the governorate's security operations for this purpose. 
  We hope everyone will comply and cooperate. It is God who 
grants success. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

