<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Condolences Sent to France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Condolences Sent to France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805205794 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0805205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the assassination of two French nationals 
in the capital Algiers today, Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi sent a 
cable of condolences to his French counterpart, Edouard 
Balladur, on behalf of the government and in his personal name, 
which stated that the Algerian authorities will do their utmost 
to arrest the perpetrators of this crime. This is no more than 
a confirmation, the head of government adds, regarding combating 
terrorism. 
  The interior minister has deplored, in a statement released 
this evening, this abominable action and offered condolences to 
the families of the two victims and the whole of the French 
community regarding this tragic incident. 
  The interior minister stressed that Algeria is known for its 
tradition of hospitality and its respect of human life and is 
not and will never be a home for criminals and killers. The 
perpetrators of this operation will be sought and punished 
severely, he said. 
  Regarding the terrorist activities, the security services 
announced today that they had eliminated 15 terrorists and 
arrested 5 others between Monday and Saturday at various parts 
of the country. 

</TEXT>

