<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Passes Sentences in `Terrorism' Cases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Passes Sentences in `Terrorism' Cases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605211894 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Constantine special judicial court passed 
sentences ranging between 15 years imprisonment to the acquittal 
of 58 accused in a number of cases connected with terrorism and 
acts of sabotage. Those sentenced belonged to a number of 
terrorist organizations that carried out burglaries, desecrated 
places of worship, made home-made bombs, printed inciting 
leaflets, and other charges infringing on public security. 

</TEXT>

