<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry: Algerians in Yemen `Well' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry: Algerians in Yemen `Well' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805085294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0800 
GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0805085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a communique issued yesterday evening, the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs said that the members of the 
Algerian community living in Yemen are well. The communique 
said that Algeria's ambassador in Sanaa is in constant contact 
with the members of the Algerian community there to provide them 
with the needed help. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs reassures families who have 
relatives in Yemen that all measures have been taken in 
coordination with Algeria's embassy in Sanaa to guarantee 
consular protection for the Algerian nationals to face the 
current events in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

