<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Urges Yemen To Begin Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Urges Yemen To Begin Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705235794 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705235794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As part of Arab endeavors to contain the crisis in 
Yemen, today [7 May] Algeria reiterated its preparedness to 
contribute all it can to the settlement of the Yemeni crisis, 
calling on both sides of the conflict to stop the fighting. 
  An authorized source at the Foreign Ministry said today that 
Algeria is following the events in Yemen with concern and calls 
on both parties to the conflict to begin a dialogue. 
  The source added that because of its feeling of 
responsibility as a member state and as current president of the 
Arab Maghreb Union, Algeria has recently made a number of 
political moves in an effort to reconcile the viewpoints of the 
two parties in conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

