<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Holds Talks With Turkish President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Holds Talks With Turkish President </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Demirel Leaves Cairo for Home </H4>

<F P=102> NC0705170094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1555 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0705170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 May (MENA)-- Turkish President Suleyman 
Demirel and his delegation left Cairo for home this evening 
after a visit of several hours to Egypt. 
  He was seen off at the airport by President Husni Mubarak. 
  Earlier in the evening, the Turkish President met President 
Mubarak at the Presidential Palace, and Mubarak then accompanied 
him to the airport. 

</TEXT>

