<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Receives Call From Yemeni President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Receives Call From Yemeni President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705101694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0938 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0705101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 May (MENA)--President Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak this morning received a telephone call from Yemeni 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih who explained the developments in 
Yemen over the past 24 hours. 
  President Mubarak stressed the need to halt military 
operations between the two sides immediately, contain the 
worsening situation, and take measures to initiate a dialogue 
for the good of the Yemeni people. 
  During the telephone conversation, President Mubarak warned 
of the Yemeni arena turning into an uncontrollable all-out war. 
  Yesterday, President Mubarak addressed an appeal to the 
Yemeni leaders asking them to stop the military operations. He 
urged President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, as head of the country, to 
adopt decisions and initiatives to preserve the Yemeni people's 
interests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

