<H3> <TI>   Visit of Tunisian Foreign Minister Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of Tunisian Foreign Minister Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Terms Meeting With Mubarak `Productive' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0805102694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0900 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0805102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 May (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak 
received a message from Tunisian President Zine el-Abidine Ben 
Ali during an audience today with Habib Ben Yahya, Tunisian 
foreign minister and the Tunisian president's personal envoy, 
who is currently in Cairo. 
  The Tunisian envoy said after the meeting that the message 
is 
part of the continuous consultation and cooperation between 
Egypt and Tunisia. 
  He said the meeting was productive and that they had 
reviewed 
various African issues because the date of the forthcoming 
African summit in Tunis is approaching. He added that Tunisia 
will be honored by the participation of President Mubarak, 
current chairman of the OAU, in this summit so they can benefit 
from his experience in the African arena. 
  He said the meeting also dealt with ways to consolidate and 
develop bilateral relations and expressed his country's desire 
to arrange more meetings between the two countries' officials to 
enhance bilateral cooperation. 

</TEXT>

