<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Extends President's Decree Powers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Extends President's Decree Powers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0805141994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0805141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 8 May (MENA)--The People's Assembly held a 
meeting today chaired by Speaker Dr. Ahmad Fathi Surur. It 
approved the president of the Republic's decree extending Law 
No. 29 of 1972 empowering the president of the Republic to issue 
decrees having the strength of law. The law is extended for 
three years and expires at the end of fiscal year 1994-1996. 
The bill was opposed by 11 members of the opposition and 
independents. 
  Commenting on opposition to the bill by deputy Lutfi Wakid 
of 
the National Progressive Unionist Grouping Party, Kamal 
al-Shadhili, minister of state for the People's Assembly and 
Consultative Council affairs, said that secrecy and speed in 
approving arms deals are necessary. Thus, the president of the 
Republic was authorized to issue such decrees, noting that 
submitting the bill to the People's Assembly in accordance with 
the law takes place after the president authorizes it and while 
the authorization is still valid. He stressed that the 
circumstances the Arab nation has been passing through require 
that Egypt have a strong army. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

