<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 May (MENA)-- The Democratic Unionist Party 
today elected Ibrahim Muhammad 'Abd-al-Mun'im Turk as party 
chairman to replace Muhammad 'Abd-al-Mun'im Turk, who passed 
away recently. 
  In a statement after his election today, Turk voiced support 
for President Mubarak's successful foreign policy, which helps 
the establishment of peace in the Middle East. 
  He reiterated the party's support for the national dialogue 
called for by President Mubarak, noting that this call embodies 
the climate of democracy, freedom, and the supremacy of the law 
