<H4>    Kakizawa, Delegation Depart </H4>

<F P=102> JN0705163094 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0705163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1130 today, President Hafiz al-Asad received 
Japanese Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa and his accompanying 
delegation. Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' and the Japanese 
ambassador in Damascus attended the meeting. Talks dealt with 
the situation in the Middle East and the peace process. 
  The Japanese minister paid tribute to Syria's positive role 
in launching the peace process. He noted the regional and 
international importance of achieving a just and comprehensive 
peace in the region. The two sides also discussed bilateral 
relations and the available means to develop them in the future. 
  The Japanese official left Damascus today after a two-day 
visit to the Syrian Arab Republic. He was seen off at Damascus 
International Airport by Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', senior 
Foreign Ministry officials, and the Japanese Minister in 
Damascus. 
  In a statement to a SANA correspondent, Kakizawa said: My 
visit to Syria was very successful. I had the privilege of 
meeting with President Hafiz al-Asad and Syrian officials. He 
added that his talks dealt with the means to develop bilateral 
relations, which he described as very good. Kakizawa expressed 
the Japanese people's hopes that peace will be achieved in the 
Middle East. He also expressed Japan's willingness to cooperate 
and make a positive contribution to the peace process. 

</TEXT>

