<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Says American Woman `Probably a Spy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Says American Woman `Probably a Spy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0805103894 Paris AFP in English 0854 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0805103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 8 (AFP) -- An American woman whipped in 
Iran two weeks ago on charges of promoting prostitution is 
"probably a spy", a radical newspaper charged here Sunday. 
  Mary Jones, 35, was picked up two weeks ago in the Shemiran 
neighborhood in northern Tehran allegedly in a drunken state. 
She was immediately given 80 lashes of the whip after being 
found guilty in a court of "promoting corruption." 
  JOMHURI-YE ESLAMI daily charged however that new information 
on Jones had led the authorities to believe that she was also 
engaged in espionage. 
  She paid visits to the war front during the 1980-1988 
conflict with Iraq and made "suspicious remarks" during 
interrogation after her arrest," it said. 
  However, a revolutionary court contacted by AFP denied there 
was any evidence of espionage activities against Jones, and that 
she had been arrested on corruption charges only. 
  The U.S. interests section at the Swiss embassy in Tehran 
declined to comment on the case. 
  The daily KEYHAN charged on Thursday that Jones, who has 
been 
here since 1983, came here "without identity papers and with the 
aim of corrupting the young in Iran." 
  KEYHAN said that Jones had been ordered to leave the 
country, 
but a judiciary official at the court refused to disclose if she 
had already been deported. 
  Iran banned the sale and consumption of alcoholic drinks 
after the 1979 Islamic revolution which toppled the late shah. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

