<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Phones FRG's Kohl on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Phones FRG's Kohl on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605172194 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1430 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani in a telephone 
conversation with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl talked to him 
about the latest situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina and ways of 
expanding political and economic relations between Iran and 
Germany. 
  In this telephone conversation, the president expressed his 
anxiety about the repetition of the tragedy of Gorazde by the 
Serbs and stressed the need for a decisive and serious approach 
by the countries of the world and international organizations 
toward the Serb aggressors. 
  Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani also expressed his hope that the two 
countries will have a more active participation in the second 
economic and political development plan of Iran. 
  Mr. Kohl also said that the exchange of political and 
economic delegations between the two countries to study the 
issue of Bosnia-Herzegovina and find new ways for the expansion 
of cooperation between the two countries has always enjoyed the 
support and attention of the German Government. 

</TEXT>

