<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Majles Speaker Criticizes Israeli-PLO Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Majles Speaker Criticizes Israeli-PLO Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805085894 Tehran IRNA in English 0817 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 8, IRNA -- Majles speaker 'Ali Akbar 
Nateq-Nuri Sunday [8 May] lambasted the signing of the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement between the Zionist regime and the 
Palestine Liberation Organisation (PLO) last Wednesday and 
stressed that the Palestinian nation would not give in to 
abjection. 
  Speaking at the open sessison of the Islamic consultative 
assembly (majles), he termed the compromising trend of talks 
between Yasir 'Arafat and the Zionist regime as well as the 
signing of the Gaza-Jericho compromise deal as gradual 
humiliation of the PLO leaders and a bitter and regrettable 
development for the world of Islam and the muslims. 
  "It is crystal clear that the heroic nation of Palestine 
will 
continue their fight against occupiers of al-Quds and repulse 
the usurpers from al-Quds to materialize the divine promises," 
he stressed. 
  Turning to the victory of the African National congress in 
the all-race presidential elections in South Africa, Nateq-Nuri 
described it as a great and sweet event for all nations 
especially for the people of South Africa. 
  Congratulating the ANC leader Nelson Mandela and the South 
African nation on the victory, he expressed hope that Iran and 
South African relations would expand in all fields. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

