<F P=100> Islamic Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   ICO Views Events in Yemen With `Grave Concern' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ICO Views Events in Yemen With `Grave Concern' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805131094 Riyadh SPA in English 1226 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, May 8, SPA -- The Organization of the 
Islamic Conference (OIC) [ICO] has expressed grave concern over 
the serious escalation of the situation in the Republic of 
Yemen, especially the recent incidents in many provinces which 
have killed and wounded a large number of people. 
  In a statement issued Saturday [7 May], the OIC expressed 
hope that usual stability and cordiality among the people of 
Yemen would be restored, differences would be discarded and 
efforts would be exerted to confirm their unity and resort to 
dialogue and understanding rather than violence and fighting. 
  The OIC called on the leaders and people of Yemen to show 
restraint and remain committed to their firm belief and wisdom 
and work together for the progress of Yemen and the protection 
of its immortal civilization. 
  OIC Secretary General Dr. Hamid al-Ghabid called on Yemeni 
leaders, ulemas and politicians to work as one for the best 
interests of the country. 
  He asked them to find points of agreement and reduce points 
of disagreement and withdraw massed troops separating brothers 
to their previous positions. 
  Dr. al-Ghabid once again confirmed the OIC's readiness to 
exert good Islamic offices and mediation efforts out of its 
Islamic duty and in conformity with the principles of Islam. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

