<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alleged U.S. Preconditions for Rao Visit Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alleged U.S. Preconditions for Rao Visit Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0705145394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0705145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The talks between the prime minister, Mr. P.V. 
Narasimha Rao, and the U.S. President, Mr. Bill Clinton, on the 
19th of this month in Washington are expected to cover a wide 
range of bilateral and international issues. While stating 
this, the External Affairs Ministry spokesman said in New Delhi 
today that substantial preparations are being made to make the 
visit successful. He said the visit will lead to enhanced 
cooperation between the two countries. Denying reports in a 
section of the press about the reported ultimatum or 
preconditions being laid down by the USA for the visit of the 
prime minister, the spokesman said the report is full of errors 
and distortions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

