<H3> <TI>   Rabin Sees `United Jerusalem' in Final Arrangement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Sees `United Jerusalem' in Final Arrangement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0805184994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 8 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0805184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said he foresees a 
united Jerusalem under Israeli sovereignty and as Israel's 
capital also in the permanent arrangement with the Palestinians. 
Mr. Rabin was speaking to our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky at a 
reception hosted by Mayor Ehud Olmert at Jerusalem's City Hall 
to mark the beginning of the Jerusalem Day celebrations. 
  Mr. Rabin noted that Jerusalem is the heart of the Jewish 
people and, consequently, is the heart of hearts of the State of 
Israel. 

