<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   GCC Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GCC Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805131694 Riyadh SPA in English 1224 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, May 8, SPA -- The General Secretariat of 
the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) has issued the following 
statement on the developments of the situation in the Republic 
of Yemen: 
  "While following with grave concern and deep sorrow the 
serious and painful deteriorations in the Republic of Yemen as a 
result of the eruption of fighting and battles between brothers 
int [as received], the Gulf Cooperation Council states appeal to 
the Yemeni leaders to put the interests of Yemen and its people 
above all other considerations, put an end to the battles and 
fighting and practice the highest degrees of self-restraint to 
halt the bloodshed and protect lives and properties". 
  "They call on Yemeni leaders to respond to initiatives 
calling for an end to the fighting and resort to reason and 
dialogue to resolve differences," the statement said. 

</TEXT>

