<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Negotiator on Return of Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Negotiator on Return of Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0905145494 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 9 May 94 pp 1, 18 </F>
<F P=103> TA0905145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza -- Attorney Khalid al-Qidrah, head of the 
Cairo talks Legal Committee, has said that it has been agreed 
that all Palestinians who were registered in the Gaza Strip, the 
Jericho area, and the West Bank up to 4 June 1967 will be 
repatriated to their homeland and families. 
  Al-Qidrah said that the agreement does not include only 
those 
who resided in the West Bank and the Gaza Strip after the 
occupation and emigrated, but also those who lived there before 
the occupation. Agreement has been reached on the repatriation 
of these Palestinians as well. 
  Al-Qidrah noted that if a resident of the Gaza Strip or 
Jericho was traveling, studying, or employed abroad when the 
occupation took place, he has the right to return in accordance 
with the Declaration of Principles accord signed on 13 September. 
  Al-Qidrah said that talks over the timetable of this 
repatriation will be held within the coming days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

