<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   5 Countries Sign Electricity Grid Project Protocol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    5 Countries Sign Electricity Grid Project Protocol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0905155694 Cairo MENA in English 1410 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0905155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, May 9 (MENA)--Electricity ministers from 
Egypt, Jordan, Syria and Turkey as well as a representative from 
the Iraqi electricity minister today signed the executive 
protocol of the Arab Mashreq Power Grid project. 
  The signing came at the end of ministerial meetings of the 
five countries, which opened yesterday under the chairmanship of 
Egyptian Minister of Electricity Mahir Abazah. 
  Under the protocol, the signatories will ask the Arab Fund 
for Economic and Social Development for funds to finance the 
project. 
  Abazah said feasibility studies have favored the Arab 
Mashreq 
Power Grid. 
  The upcoming session of the electricity ministers will be 
held in Ankara in April 1995. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

