<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Forces Arrive in Rafah from Saudi Arabia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Forces Arrive in Rafah from Saudi Arabia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0905204694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2020 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0905204694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Rafah, 9 May (MENA)--Six Saudi Air Force planes 
landed at al-Jawrah Airport near Rafah this evening carrying 
about 450 Palestinian police members. The force arrived in 
Saudi Arabia from Yemen by an overland route. Another plane 
arrived carrying RPG's and Kalashnikov rifles in closed boxes. 
[passage omitted] 
  This is the second group of Palestinian forces to arrive in 
Rafah on the international border with Israel. About 350 men 
arrived yesterday from the al-Yarmuk Camp in Cairo. 
  Other forces from Yemen, Sudan, and Libya will arrive in 
Rafah tomorrow. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

