<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Force Expected To Enter Jericho 10 or 11 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Force Expected To Enter Jericho 10 or 11 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0905171194 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 1600 
GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0905171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Palestinian police force awaiting Israeli 
permission to deploy in Jericho was delayed for a second day 
today, pending inspection of the weapons they plan to bring. 
PLO Ambassador to Jordan al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim said the 
police will enter tomorrow or the day after tomorrow. 
  The 270 police who were to be the first contingent were 
joined early today by another 430 Palestinian soldiers. 
Meanwhile, a first contingent of the Palestinian police force 
camped on the Egyptian side of the border and was expected to 
enter Gaza later today. 

</TEXT>

