<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraq-Based Palestinian Forces Enters Jordan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraq-Based Palestinian Forces Enters Jordan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805180694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 8 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first group from the al-Aqsa forces of the 
Palestine Liberation Army stationed on Iraqi territory arrived 
at the border post of al-Karamah-al-Ruwayshid this morning en 
route to the occupied territories. This group is composed of 
600 officers, non-commissioned officers, and other ranks. 
  Palestinian Ambassador in Amman al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim said 
these forces' entry at the al-Ruwayshid border post came at the 
request of the Palestinian leadership. His Majesty King Husayn 
ordered that all necessary facilities be provided to these 
forces during their stay on Jordanian territory, and that they 
be treated as the guests of the Jordanian Armed Forces, which 
will equip and arm them. 
  In a statement to the JORDANIAN NEWS AGENCY, the ambassador 
added that both Jordan's permission for this group to enter 
Jordanian territory and the provision of the necessary 
assistance to them are definitive proof of the true and profound 
fraternity between the sisterly Jordanian and Palestinian 
peoples and their common fate. Moreover, this confirms the 
eagerness of the Hashemite leadership, represented by His 
Majesty King Husayn, to enable the sons of the Palestinian 
people to achieve their national objectives on their national 
soil under the leadership of the PLO. 
  This group was welcomed by representatives from the 
Jordanian 
Armed Forces and by the Palestinian military attache at the 
Palestinian Embassy in Amman. 
  In another development, 'Abd-al-Rahim said the Palestinian 
police forces' entry into Gaza and Jericho areas is linked to 
the announcment of the formation of the Palestinian national 
authority. The Palestinian leadership is continuing its meetings 
in the Tunisian capital to officially form this authority, he 
added. 
  The Palestinian ambassador attributed the delay in the 
Palestinian police forces' entry into Gaza and Jericho areas 
today to technical reasons linked to the Israeli procedures 
concerning these forces' weapons. He explained that contacts 
are continuing in this regard between the heads of the 
Palestinian and Israeli negotiating delegations, Sha'th and 
Shahaq. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

