<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Appoints Security Chiefs for West Bank, Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Appoints Security Chiefs for West Bank, Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0905072094 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0905072094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Informed Palestinian sources in Tunis have told our 
correspondent Yoni Ben-Menahem that during the recent Cairo 
talks the PLO agreed not to put Palestinian collaborators on 
trial but refused to grant them a pardon. It is expected that 
the file of the collaborators will be handled by Jibril 
al-Rujub, Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, who has been appointed as the 
official responsible for the West Bank's preventive security 
[al-amn al-wiqa'i]. Al-Rujub is expected to return to the 
territories next Friday. Moreover, Muhammad Dahlan, member of 
the PLO Gaza Committee, has been appointed as the official 
responsible for the Gaza Strip's preventive security. 

</TEXT>

