<H3> <TI>   Hamas Rejects Agreements, Vows Continued Struggle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Rejects Agreements, Vows Continued Struggle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0905151394 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 8 May 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PM0905151394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Hamas Vows To Continue Its </F>
Operations, Warns Against `One-Party System'"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-HAYAH -- The Islamic Resistance 
Movement (Hamas) yesterday vowed to continue its operations 
against the Israeli occupation despite the agreement signed by 
the PLO and Israel in Cairo to implement self-rule in Gaza and 
Jericho. It described the agreement as "capitulationist, null 
and void, and not binding on the Palestinian people." 
  In a statement, of which AL-HAYAH has received a copy, Hamas 
urged the Palestinian authority and its police to serve the 
people. It warned of "the consequences of factionalism, a 
one-party system, submitting to the Zionist enemy, and 
preventing our people's mujahidin from carrying out resistance 
operations against the occupation army and settlers." 
  Hamas welcomed "dialogue and meeting with all Palestinian 
national forces and influential figures on the basis of 
continuing the resistance, defeating the occupation, and sparing 
our people the calamities of sedition and infighting." It 
condemned "the use of arms to resolve political and family 
disputes." 
  Hamas vowed to continue mass struggle "against the 
occupation 
and its symbols." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

