<F P=106> [Linda Sherzer video report; italicized passages in English] </F>
  [Excerpts] Dr. Fathi al-Shaqaqi, the Palestinian Islamic 
Jihad leader, maintains that navigator Ron Arad is the only IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] soldier missing in Lebanon who is still 
alive. Al-Shaqaqi made this observation in an interview with 
Linda Sherzer in Damascus last week. He contends that he does 
not know where Ron Arad is being held today. Here is Linda 
Sherzer's report from Syria: 
  [Begin recording] [Sherzer] Before Fathi al-Shaqaqi was 
expelled from the Gaza Strip, he was considered one of the most 
dangerous people there. In his office in Damascus, he proudly 
explains the reason: 
