<F P=103> NC0905182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Muslim Brotherhood has appealed to the parties 
to the conflict in Yemen to safeguard the public interest and 
settle their differences within the framework of a constructive 
dialogue based on God's shari'ah and to place Yemeni unity above 
any other consideration. In a statement released by the Muslim 
Brotherhood, it called on the Arab and Muslim rulers and all 
Arab and Muslim organizations to play the required role to close 
the Yemeni ranks and stop the bloodshed. 
  The Muslim Brotherhood expressed its worry about the 
deterioration of the situation in Yemen and the threat to Yemeni 
unity. It noted that the fraternal Yemeni people's property and 
resources are threatened. It stressed the need to pool efforts 
and resources to heal the rift in Yemen and bring the parties 
together in the interest of that country and its unity and its 
people's security, freedom, lives, and generation's resources. 

</TEXT>

