<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Seize Weapons Factory, Equipment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0905193394 Cairo AL-AHRAM AL-MASA'I in Arabic 6 May 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> NC0905193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM AL-MASA'I </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Al-Qalyubiyah detectives yesterday seized a 
weapons factory in Kafr Shukr in a surprise raid on the Shubra 
al-Khaymah and Kafr Shukr areas. The raid also resulted in the 
arrest of six dangerous drug traffickers and 25 people suspected 
of involvement in criminal cases. [passage omitted] 
  Large forces from the Central Security Agency, led by Deputy 
Director of al-Qalyubiyah Security Major General Sabri Shindi, 
Detective Department Director Brigadier General Taha al-Zahid, 
and Detective Chief Colonel Muhammad Rahim stormed the weapons 
factory in a basement of a house in Marakz Kafr Shukr owned by a 
dangerous person with a police record. Some 15 weapons, five 
live ammunition magazines, and equipment for manufacturing 
various types of weapons for sale to criminals and drug 
traffickers in the area were seized. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

