<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Injure 2 at Police Checkpoint </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0905131794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1250 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0905131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 9 May (MENA)--A security source in the 
Interior Ministry has stated that at around 0900 this morning, 
unknown gunmen opened fire on the checkpoint outside the Sadafa 
police station in Asyut Governorate in Upper Egypt. Two 
citizens who were passing by were slightly injured and taken to 
hospital for treatment. 
  The source said that the Asyut security department command 
and the investigations department went to scene of the incident. 
The source noted that the police are continuing their efforts 
to arrest the perpetrators. The prosecution has been informed 
and started investigating the incident immediately. 

