<H4>    Port Reportedly Functioning Normally </H4>

<F P=102> EA0905192194 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1630 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0905192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Muhammad Bin-Muhammad Shakir, the acting 
director general of the port of Aden, has stated that operations 
at the port have been uninterrupted and are proceeding normally. 
In a statement to the Yemeni news agency, SABA', he referred to 
reports put out by a number of news agencies, to the effect that 
the port had been closed. He said that the port's operations 
had been proceeding normally without interruption, noting that 
the port was open to international navigation and was providing 
full services to all ships reaching it from other ports. 
Brother Muhammad Bin-Muhammad Shakir went on to say that a 
number of ships carrying various types of cargo were outside the 
port, and were awaiting their turn to enter the port when other 
ships had completed discharging their cargoes. 

</TEXT>

