<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Interviewed on Fighting, Vows To `Hold Out' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Interviewed on Fighting, Vows To `Hold Out' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1005074594 London MBC Television in Arabic 2100 GMT 9 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1005074594 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, </F>
in Aden, by MBC correspondent Ahmad Manjuna on 9 May -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Manjuna] Can Yemen endure the ongoing fighting 
developing into a protracted war of attrition? 
  [Al-Bid] We want to implement the Pledge and Accord 
Document. 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his forces reject this. Failing to 
implement the document, they resorted to war to impose another 
course on the Yemeni people. We will all abide by the document 
around which the overwhelming majority of the Yemeni people 
rally. Even those who have been forcibly sent to the war by 
'Abdallah Salih are now fighting with low morale because they 
are not convinced about what they are doing. They do not know 
what they are doing. What are their objectives when they advance 
toward particular areas in the southern provinces? 
  [Manjuna] Brother 'Ali: How can you describe the military 
situation? And how can you hold out? 
  [Al-Bid] We will hold out. But we are convinced that whoever 
triumphs in this war will still be a loser. But what can we do? 
As long as this war is imposed on us we will defend ourselves 
and we will adhere to the course we have chosen. We have chosen 
the road of unity, democracy, civil rule, and equality. We also 
chose the Pledge and Accord Document on the basis of national 
unanimity. We will adhere to this document and we will fight to 
ensure that it is implemented. 
  [Manjuna] Despite the signing of the Pledge and Accord 
Document, the government in Sanaa accuses the southerners of 
secession and mutiny. On what grounds does the government in 
Sanaa base its accusations? 
  [Al-Bid] This is their understanding of issues and it shows 
their miscalculations. We opted for unity. We dissolved our 
regime here in the south and we took our units from here to 
Sanaa. Regrettably, they were besieged and attacked in Sanaa. 
We did not do all this. The Yemeni people know this. History 
will be the judge. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

