<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Issues Decree, Dismisses Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Issues Decree, Dismisses Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005055594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Presidential Council Decree No. 11 issued on 9 May -- read </F>
by announcer] 
  [Text] The chairman of the Presidential Council, cognizant 
of the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen; in view Prime 
Minister Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas' actions, which 
violate constitutional legitimacy, and his abuse of office by 
exposing the homeland's sovereignty and independence to threats, 
such as his conduct that was discussed by the House of 
Representatives, which issued recommendations to the Executive 
Authority to adopt the necessary measures in accordance with the 
Constitution; and in view of the requirements of public interest 
and after the approval of the President Council, decrees the 
following: 
<H5>  Article I. </H5>
  Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the prime minister, 
shall 
be dismissed from his office and shall be referred to 
interrogation in accordance with Article 111 of the Republic of 
Yemen Constitution. 
<H5>  Article II. </H5>
  This decree will be valid as of date of issue and will be 
published in the official gazette. 
  Issued at the Presidency in Sanaa on 29 Dhu al-Qi'dah, 1414 
of the hegira, 9 May 1994. 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of 
the President Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

