<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-'Attas Rejects Dismissal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-'Attas Rejects Dismissal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1005094094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1005094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the office of Council of 
Ministers Chairman Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas has made a 
statement to the Yemeni news agency, SABA'. He said in the 
statement that there have been successive improvised and biased 
decisions from 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, the latest of which is a 
decision announced through the Sanaa news media to suspend Prime 
Minister Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas and to charge another person 
to carry out his duties. Earlier 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih issued a 
number of decisions suspending Defense Minister Haytham Qasim 
Tahir, Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun, minister of oil and mineral 
resources, and Aden Governor Salih Munassar al-Syayli. 
  The source said this type of decision reflects the state of 
bewilderment experienced by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih after his 
ill-fated decision to drown Yemen in a bloody war. He pointed 
out that these decisions not only contradict the Constitution 
which he trampled under foot when he declared the war, but also 
reflect the psychology of defeat which has controlled his mind 
following the setbacks suffered by the forces of his gang in 
more than one military position. He is now trying to patch up 
his shaky position before those he promised to occupy Aden 
within a few hours. 
  The source confirmed that these decisions have been rejected 
in their entirety because they violate the Constitution and go 
against it. He clarified that confidence in the prime minister 
can only be withdrawn by the house of deputies. The ministers 
cannot be dismissed except publicly and with the prime 
minister's consent. When this occurs or when the prime minister 
resigns himself, the entire Council of Ministers must be 
considered as having resigned. 
  The source wondered: What can we expect from the man who 
ignited the war, the strife, and the civil war? What can we 
expect from the man who directs his guns against the citizens 
and children and stabs at the very heart of unity? What can we 
expect other than these stupid decisions through which he is 
implementing his secessionist goals. 
  The source ridiculed such decisions and said they have no 
impact whatsoever after the war decision adopted by 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih. He pointed out that these decisions are 
additions to the declaration of war by means of which he 
announced the liquidation of unity and the liquidation of 
everything that would remind him of it. 
  The source concluded by saying that all the decisions issued 
by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih are constitutionally invalid and are 
(?capricious) and unrecognized. He said that the theatrical 
farce being implemented by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his gang 
after the war decision cannot fool anybody, particularly as he 
cancelled the legitimacy of unity and adopted a secessionist 
decision by declaring war on 27 April. It is a decision he will 
not be permitted to achieve because unity is the will of the 
people, and they will defend it to the last breath of life. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

