<H3> <TI>   Salih Appoints Al-'Attar Acting Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Appoints Al-'Attar Acting Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005055094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005055094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Presidential Council Decree No. 12 issued on 9 May -- read </F>
by announcer] 
  [Text] The chairman of the Presidential Council, cognizant 
of the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen; in view of the 
dismissal of Prime Minister Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas', 
and in view of the requirements of public interest and after the 
approval of the President Council, decrees the following: 
<H5>  Article I. </H5>
  Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, deputy prime minister, will be 
charged with the duties of the prime minister. 
<H5>  Article II. </H5>
  This decree will be valid as of date of issue and will be 
published in the official gazette. 
  Issued at the Presidency in Sanaa on 29 Dhu al-Qi'dah, 1414 
of the hegira, 9 May 1994. 
  [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of 
the President Council 

</TEXT>

