<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Members Reportedly Detained </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Members Reportedly Detained </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1005105594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1900 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1005105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to eye witness reports, many headquarters 
of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] in the governorates of 
Ta'izz, Ibb, Sanaa, Dhamar, Hajjah, Sa'dah, Mahwit, and 
al-Hudaydah have been taken over and converted to centers for 
detaining YSP members, other patriotic and democratic parties 
supporting it, and members of the gang of the al-Ahmar clan who 
support the pledge and accord document. 
  These reports further state that ambushes are being laid for 
YSP members who are heading for their party centers. They are 
deceived into entering the centers and are then detained. 
Reports by people coming from the northern governorates say 
that this same method is being used on members of other parties 
participating in the dialogue committee, outside the [word 
indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

