<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Allocates 5 Million Dinars for Poor Families </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Allocates 5 Million Dinars for Poor Families </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0905140394 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0905140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn has ordered the 
allocation of 5 million dinars for poor families within the 
geographic area of the al-Rashid Branch Command of the Arab 
Socialist Ba'th Party. 
  Comrade Fadil Mashhadani, secretary of the al-Rashid Branch 
of the Ba'th Party, told an INA correspondent that this generous 
contribution on the part of leader President Saddam Husayn 
embodies his excellency's care for the sons of his people to 
ease their suffering as a result of the continuation of the 
unjust blockade. 
  He said the people's councils, in coordination with the 
party's agencies, have started distributing the president's 
contribution to poor families in al-Karradah, Baghdad 
al-Jadidah, al-Mashtal, al-Za'faraniyah, al-Mada'in, and al-Amin. 

</TEXT>

