<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Delhi To Boost Ties With Israel, Palestinians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi To Boost Ties With Israel, Palestinians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1005092894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1005092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India has expressed its desire to develop closer and 
stronger bilateral relations with Israel and Palestine. This 
view was expressed in separate meetings the vice president, Mr. 
K.R. Narayanan, had with the Israeli president, Mr. Weizman, and 
the PLO chief, Mr. Yasir 'Arafat, in Johannesburg yesterday. 
  In his meeting with Mr. 'Arafat, Mr. Narayanan offered 
India's support in the reconstruction and development of 
Palestine after the situation settles down in the region. India 
has already pledged $1 million in kind during the international 
donors meeting in Cairo. New Delhi has also offered 15 
additional training positions for paramedical staff from 
Palestine. 

</TEXT>

