<H3> <TI>   Citizens in Yemen `Safe'; Embassy Aiding Evacuees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Citizens in Yemen `Safe'; Embassy Aiding Evacuees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1005110394 Delhi THE HINDUSTAN TIMES in English 7 May 94 p 
12 </F>

<F P=103> BK1005110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi THE HINDUSTAN TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi -- The 7,000 strong Indian community in 
Yemen is safe and some of them have expressed a desire to leave 
the strife-torn country, an official spokesman said today, 
according to UNI. 
  The Indian embassy in Sanaa is assisting the Indian 
nationals 
to leave Yemen where fierce fighting has erupted between North 
and South Yemeni forces. 
  India has expressed sincere hope that peaceful conditions 
will be rapidly restored and all differences resolved on the 
basis of the Amman reconciliation agreement signed in February. 

</TEXT>

