<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   House Commends French Decision on Naval Inspections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Commends French Decision on Naval Inspections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0905145594 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 9 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0905145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives has commended the 
existing positive and distinguished relations between Jordan and 
France based on mutual understanding and respect. In a 
statement issued today, the House of Representatives said it was 
satisfied with the French Government's decision to stop its 
participation in naval inspections at the Port of al-'Aqabah. 
Following is the text of the House of Representatives' 
statement: 
  The Jordanian House of Representatives received with some 
satisfaction the statements by the French Foreign Ministry's 
spokesman on Wednesday, 4 May 1994, which deal with the French 
Government's decision to stop its participation in naval 
inspections at the Port of al-'Aqabah. 
  Although the House of Representatives believes that this 
step 
is somewhat late, it still considers it a positive step since it 
shows the French Government's understanding and awareness of 
Jordan's sound policies, just demands, and firm and principled 
stands. 
  Moreover, the House of Representatives hopes that the French 
Government's decision will be the first step, followed by 
similar steps by other countries participating in the naval 
inspections, toward lifting the siege imposed on the Port of 
al-'Aqabah and compensating Jordan for the serious losses it has 
suffered as a result of these inspections. 
  As the Jordanian House of Representatives is fully aware of 
the international changes and developments and of the fact that 
only one superpower is imposing its decisions and its own 
interpretation on others, and it hopes that the French 
Government will take another step by exerting more effort and 
playing a more effective role to implement the resolutions of 
international legitimacy in a just and unbiased manner. 
  At the same time, the Jordanian House of Representatives 
commended the existing positive and distinguished relations 
between Jordan and France based on mutual understanding and 
respect and the House called for the continuous development of 
these relations. 

</TEXT>

