<H3> <TI>   Official Welcomes France's Decision </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Welcomes France's Decision </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805081494 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 8 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0805081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, PETRA--Jordan yesterday welcomed the French 
Government's decision to suspend its participation in the naval 
inspection operations in al-'Aqabah Port. 
  This came in a statement by the Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, 
minister of state for foreign affairs, in answer to a question 
by the Jordanian News Agency. He said this decision was 
announced in a statement by the French Foreign Ministry's 
spokesman on Wednesday [4 May] on France's decision to halt its 
participation in naval inspection operations in al-'Aqabah Port. 
  Al-Hasan said the decision reflects France's understanding 
of 
Jordan's positive and constructive role in the region and the 
fairness of its request to reconsider the mechanism for 
implementing the embargo, which inflicted major losses on the 
Jordanian economy. The decision, he said, also reflect France's 
compliance with the resolutions of international legitimacy and 
its conviction that Jordan is fulfilling all of its commitments 
and responsibilities toward the implementation of these 
resolutions. 
  Al-Hasan also praised the distinguished relations that are 
based on understanding and mutual respect between Jordan and 
France and the ties of close friendship between His Majesty King 
Husayn and His Excellency President Francois Mitterrand. 

</TEXT>

